    "John Trapp": "We have sinned. ] Here was confession of sin, without confusion for sin. So was that of Saul. { #1Sa 15:30 }\nVer.\n40. We have sinned.] Here was confession of sin, without confusion for sin. So was that of Saul. {#1Sa 15:30}\nVer.",
    "Unknown": "PARALLEL III. Christ hath, in him a preserving quality or power; were it not for that life he has communicated to us, for the rest of mortals, how soon would our bodies rot? But in a special manner he preserves our souls. Sin is of a rotting, stinking, and putrefying nature, [v_Isa_1_5] [v_Isa_1_6] compared to a leprosy, and filthy sores, Isa 1:5-"
